                            <comment id="12995441" author="rhillegas" created="Wed, 16 Feb 2011 18:27:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a discussion about reasonable defaults for the undocumented istat knobs and about whether additional knobs are needed: &lt;a href=&quot;http://old.nabble.com/forum/Search.jtp?forum=105&amp;amp;local=y&amp;amp;query=question+about+istats+thresholds&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://old.nabble.com/forum/Search.jtp?forum=105&amp;amp;local=y&amp;amp;query=question+about+istats+thresholds&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is a place to continue those discussions and, if necessary, to hang patches. At the moment, we are still planning to not document these knobs. Instead, we would like to gain experience about how istat behaves in the wild. From that experience, we hope to figure out whether these are the right knobs, how to set reasonable defaults for them, and whether we should document how to override Derby&apos;s defaults. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12995775" author="kristwaa" created="Thu, 17 Feb 2011 11:58:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch 1a, which changes the default setting of the absdiff threshold to 1000. This will hopefully stop the tinderbox and the nightlies to fail due to failures in the various updatelocks tests.&lt;br/&gt;
Whether the absdiff mechanism will be kept or not is up for discussion, this commit is primarily to try to stabilize the regression tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk with revision 1071588.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13465744" author="mamtas" created="Fri, 28 Sep 2012 18:08:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Kristian, I noticed that you committed a patch which was for regression tests. Do we plan on doing more work on this jira? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13466716" author="kristwaa" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2012 11:04:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Given that we haven&apos;t gotten much feedback from users, I assume the current defaults are ok.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m resolving this issue as Won&apos;t Fix and closing it, but users should feel free to reopen it or log a new issue at a later time if the defaults turn out to be problematic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
